HEADWORD: Keelfat
<hw>Keel"fat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Keel</ets> to
cool + <ets>fat</ets> a large tub, a vat.]</ety> <fld>(Brewing)</fld>
<def>A cooler; a vat for cooling wort, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>keelvat</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

